<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - PROSTAR&#8482; - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - Headlight Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Headlight Assembly</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Assembly - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0901131" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901131.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Headlight Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WIRING HARNESS CONNECTORS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MARKER LIGHT CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT MOUNT NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. HOOD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect three connectors from rear of headlight assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn marker light connector &#188; turn counterclockwise and remove from headlight
                    housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two bolts and wire harness P-clip from hood and headlight assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two nuts from hood and headlight assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove headlight assembly from hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Assembly - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install headlight assembly in hood opening and secure with two nuts (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_26.xml" xrefid="f0901139">Figure 46, Items 3 and 5</hotlnk>). Torque nuts
                    to 4 lbf-ft (5 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two bolts and wire harness P-clip through hood and secure headlight assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_26.xml" xrefid="f0901139">Figure 46, Items 4 and 5</hotlnk>). Torque bolts
                    to 4 lbf-ft (5 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install marker light connector into headlight assembly opening and turn clockwise &#188;
                    turn to lock in headlight assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_26.xml" xrefid="f0901139">Figure 46, Items 2 and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect three electrical connectors to rear of headlight assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_26.xml" xrefid="f0901139">Figure 46, Items 1 and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Bulb Replacement</title>
            <figure id="f0901132" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901132.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Headlight Bulbs</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT BULBS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TURN SIGNAL BULB</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MARKER LIGHT MOUNT HOLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove turn signal and headlight bulbs from headlight assembly, turn counterclockwise
                    and remove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install turn signal and headlight bulbs into proper positions in headlight assembly and
                    turn clockwise to lock in position.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight Adjustment</title>
            <para>The horizontal adjustment for the headlights is set at the factory and no adjustment is needed.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust the headlight vertical direction, release hood latch and tilt hood forward.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate adjustment control stem on rear of headlight housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the adjustment screw clockwise or counterclockwise to adjust the vertical
                    adjustment of the headlight beam.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
